{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/renderingserver\/viewportscaling3dmode\/fsr"]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"case","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fsr","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Case","title":"RenderingServer.ViewportScaling3DMode.fsr","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot15RenderingServerC21ViewportScaling3DModeO3fsryA2EmF"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingServer\/ViewportScaling3DMode\/fsr","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"Use AMD FidelityFX Super Resolution 1.0 upscaling for the viewport’s 3D buffer. The amount of scaling can be set using ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Viewport\/scaling3dScale"},{"type":"text","text":". Values less than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" will be result in the viewport being upscaled using FSR. Values greater than "},{"code":"1.0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are not supported and bilinear downsampling will be used instead. A value of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" disables scaling."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"case"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fsr"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/RenderingServer":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RenderingSer